text: Sheridan County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. As of the 2020 census, 5,127 people lived there. The county seat is Rushville. The county was formed in 1885 and named after General Philip H. Sheridan. Retrieved on March 15, 2008. It is the fourth-largest county in Nebraska by area. == References == Category:1885 establishments in Nebraska Category:Nebraska counties
title: Sheridan County, Nebraska
